</span><hr size=1> I started a shade a while back but without considering the BG. <br>
<br>
Not sure I can make this work but would appreciate some advice on my current template to make him battle ready in the BG when he’s level 24. <br>
<br>
Level 20 Shade <br>
20 Blades <br>
20 Envenom <br>
5 CS (I had planned on hitting this hard in later levels) <br>
5 Stealth (2 points were auto-trained) <br>
<br>
I know I need to raise my stealth heavy over the next 4 levels so this was what I was thinking at 24: <br>
<br>
At level 24… <br>
20 Blades <br>
20 Envenom (lethal poison) <br>
5 CS <br>
21 Stealth (2 points auto-trained) <br>
<br>
or… <br>
<br>
At level 24… <br>
20 Blades <br>
22 Envenom (would give me minor enervating) <br>
6 CS (this would give me first low level 3 style chain) <br>
19 Stealth (2 points auto-trained) <br>
<br>
My questions… <br>
<br>
Which of the two above would be my best bet? <br>
<br>
Would it be worth using the second template to use the MINOR Enervating Poison…is the level 22 enervating worth it or would the level 20 lethal be fine for battleground? <br>
<br>
Assuming I went with 22 enervating, what poison would I use on my primary and secondary weapons? <br>
<br>
Can you use at item to raise your envenom, apply the poison you were able to reach with the item, take off the item, and still have the poison remain on the weapon? <br>
<br>
Assuming I had 6 CS, would I even bother using the low level (2, 4, and 6) chain or use my stronger blade styles and forget about CS? <br>
<br>
Would my stealth be high enough in either case? <br>
<br>
Am I screwed with what I have to work with? <br>
<br>
Can I be effective with high weapon, high stealth, high Env, but LOW CS?  I guess that's what I need to know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=tali>Tali</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/4/02 9:48:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Level 20-24 BG: Need advice as a Shade please... </span><hr size=1> a NS with high blade skill is unusual ... I would love to hear how it goes in the BGs.<br>
<br>
At BG1 level, you can get +2 points of stealth gear pretty easily. So either stealth option will be okay.<br>
<br>
But, with little in CS, you are NOT going to be a scouting assasin. (~looks at that Envenom again~). Hmm, I could be wrong there. I think you'd likely be an effective but often-dead assasin (yer target dies shortly after you ;)<br>
<br>
If you go with this template .... I'd recommend lots o' strength buffs and items ... and set yourself up as a bodyguard. Defense of your realm's vulnerable backside (the casters ;) With over 16 spec in stealth, you'll be able to spot sneaky assasins regularly, and shout 'm out for the casters to take down, and melee the others to death. (i.e., get fantastic armor).<br>
<br>
~Tali <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufaeralspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faeral Spirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/5/02 10:15:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Level 20-24 BG: Need advice as a Shade please... </span><hr size=1> I was a high CS/Stealth, low Env NS in the BG at 24th level and found I had trouble killing most anything except casters.  Other assassins were tough and many killed me first despite my getting PA in first.  It convinced me to raise my Envenom to be able to stick and run, as this turned out to be my most successful tactic.  Since my Env was low, I often watched my prey struggle off and recover just with a few Hits left as the poison ran out.  Unless I was sure my target was alone, I would hit PA, shout, Garrotte and let my second weapon hit to deploy its poison, then run and try to stealth away.  If I thought they were alone or far enough away from help, I'd do the above, then switch to my third weapon with its poison and duke it out with Garrotte.  As the BGs mostly have stealthers, I had decreasing success killing other assassins, as they hit for unbelievably more than I did, even if I got PA off first.  <br>
<br>
High stealth was a must.  I obtained a +2 stealth item from 23-24th level and the difference was very noticeable.  I was getting seen frequently at 23rd level (with stealth at 22) and saw the reverse at 24th level, with stealth at 25.  I had enemy characters walk through me and keep going and I had lots more success discoverying stealthed enemies.  This is all subjective, but was very noticeable to me.<br>
<br>
 <p>Faeral Spirit<BR>
Nightshade<bR>
Hibernian Irregulars<BR>
Guinevere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lakeb>Lakeb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/9/02 8:35:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> poison shade</span><hr size=1> I too am a poison shade, and I too am about your level.  I thought about BG a lot when constructing my template and my current stats are 21 are:<br>
<br>
Stealth 16<br>
Pierce 15<br>
Env. 18<br>
CD 6<br>
CS 7<br>
<br>
I think you made the right call, the main thing you will want is see hidden.  By 24 I will have second back stab chain.<br>
<br>
My logic was that no one in under 24 bg gets PA and a few get Garrott and I have Greater imballance poison so I will not miss garrott, I don't think.  Personally, I feel that Greater imballance makes Garrott too costly in End when you could just use a poison for what seems to be an identical effect.  Eventually, we will face those with purge which will throw off poison, but by then we will have Garrott.<br>
<br>
With the spec we share, (not counting blades vs. pierce) I would suggest GI poison and DOT, melee till you have half your life and then run for cover.  Most players in low level BG have a messed up template and they can't respec till 25 so we should be ahead in RPs with Poison Shade template.<br>
<br>
I get as many str and con items as I can and then the rest are dex/qui.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/urehklo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rehklo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/10/02 3:32:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: poison shade</span><hr size=1> I play with garikk in the BG a lot.  I have high CS / Pierce and he has high env / blades.  <br>
<br>
Both of us have 20+ stealth and I can tell yah we suck verily.<br>
<br>
Alone I really can't kill anything execpt a lone mage (really how often does that happen, eh?)  When we're together we can take out single targets,  stragglers and such.  I PA, he poisons we run away and laugh when the guy drops dead - or curse when he gets a heal.   With CS I can also take out weekened, or new rez targets that are sitting down.... overall though, Shadowblades kick our asses on a regular basis - embarassingly so.  I mean really embarassingly so, like toe to toe no freekin chance.<br>
<br>
<br>
All in all I'm glad I made a nightshade to 24, since I really have a good feeling for what the class is all about now.  We're not the stealthy puma laying in wait to ambush our prey.  Rather a better metaphore is that we are the bottomfeeders of the realms, the carrion buzzard who feeds on decaying flesh to sustain itself. <br>
<br>
<br>
Sure we have our place, detecting other stealthers - protecting our casters, preventing theyre new-rezzes from hanging on the open field, and jumping out when someone else is in a 1 on 1 to tip the scales of battle, but in general its not a class I'd want to play passed 24. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufaeralspirit.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Faeral Spirit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(5/11/02 12:42:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: poison shade</span><hr size=1> I have to add that things change as you level higher.  While eating dirt at the APK after a large Alb army charged through, I watched Jaeden kill 5 stragglers in a row as they came through and thought to join their fellows at the AMF.  These were not all casters, some had a friend with them and at least one was a fighter type.  She was rockin'!  <br>
<br>
Standing outside a keep, supposedly defending it, and watching the banners change realms after a group of enemy stealthers killed the Lord...that's power as well.<br>
<br>
Level up... <p>Faeral Spirit<BR>
Nightshade<bR>
Hibernian Irregulars<BR>
Guinevere</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ushaftoe.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shaftoe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/9/02 12:36:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: poison shade</span><hr size=1> <br>
Each and every NS I've encountered in the 24 BG on Palomides has been spanked utterly and completely by my inf. <br>
<br>
I suggest logging onto Palomides and asking all the NSs in the BG what their template is then doing something different.<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lakeb>Lakeb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/10/02 8:39:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> poison shade</span><hr size=1> I am now 23 and I totally hurt people as a poison shade.  My stats are:<br>
<br>
Stealth 16<br>
Pierce 16+4<br>
Env: 20<br>
CD: 6<br>
CS:13<br>
<br>
I don't own people but I win more than half of my fights.  My envenom does 30 damage per tick and since most people run from you when attacked in BG, it is nice to basically be getting free hits while they run.  Last night I killed an even con minstrel with the help of a void eld... mezzed me, mezzed eld, started hitting eld, mez wore off... dead minstrel.<br>
<br>
