<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/02 10:57:55 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: poison shade</span><hr size=1> Nightshades are tough in the lower levels. And the toughest assassin class to play IMO. You can be very effective, but it just requires a tremendous amout of patience. <br>
<br>
Im not sure how viable your template will be. I would definately have your stealth at 23 or 24. You can bet yer arse that there will be several Infiltrators in the BG at any given time. Most of them will have max stealth and most will have PA, and most will have a respectable envenom. I'll put it to ya this way. My 24 Inf is gonna look like this:<br>
<br>
Stealth 23(20 +3 in items)<br>
CS 22(21 +1 in items)<br>
Thrust 21(17 +4 in items)<br>
Envenom 15<br>
DW 4<br>
<br>
I think thats a pretty standard template. And this is without twinking. Im new to the server so I cant twink, but if I could I could have 25+ in stealth and probably 20+ in Envenom. And the BGs are normally loaded with twinks. <br>
<br>
You go in there with a 19 stealth your gonna struggle as the Infiltrators will get the jump on you. Its gonna be tough no matter how ya spec. Not only are infiltrators a strong class, but again, there is no shortage of them in them in the BGs, and most work together. I really wouldnt try to work alone in there as a Shade.<br>
<br>
Grugen, the assassins really dont come into their own until later. For a thrust/pierce assassin, Skalds are probably the most dangerous Midgard class to take on. I got a 38 Skald, and I felt the same way you did in the BG1. I'd pray for an assassin to come at me. But that changes at higher levels. When they get the nastier poisons and Creeping death, you are gonna have your hands full. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uxumten.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Xumten</A> at: 6/11/02 10:59:29 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=lakeb>Lakeb</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/11/02 11:36:40 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> inf spec vs. NS spec</span><hr size=1> I think our spell line is supposed to offset the inf extra points... but we all know that is broken.  <br>
