<br>
Perf them, poison them, run and hide.  Watch them die. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub175.ezboard.com/uetrarnae.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Etrarnae</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://shamansofbloodmoon.homestead.com/files/purpfire3.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(6/29/02 3:52:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: inf spec vs. NS spec</span><hr size=1> I maxxed out of the BG in 2 days and the 35 BG in 4.<br>
<br>
But in the 35 BG all i did was run with a full 8 man stealth team and ambush reinfocements coming from mids PK.  3 rangers 5 NS's = 30+ dead mids/alb and not a single loss.<br>
<br>
Anyway  I had medium env and high crit with very high stealth along with a decent amount into pierce.  I could almost solo anyone out there except other assassins it all depended on who got the perf off.  The secret to the BG's are that you dont stick around to go h2h with them you hit move off stealth and come back. If you do stick around to fight keep straifing (sp?) around them so they cant get you in LOS (line of sight for the people who dont know) 90% of the time they have no clue how to deal with that and end up just standing there freaking out.  If they do start to turn with you switch directions. Note: this only works if you are /stick to them.<br>
<br>
Also if you want to try the ambush thing.  set 2 rangers on one side of the road close to where the trees end closest to mid PK and one on the other while the 5 NS's stand in the road watching all directions all most on top of each other.  Dont go after a too large of group we got lucky and took out a group of 8 due to killing the healers first.  Restealth after they are dead and dont move off.  More will come to rez the dead but they almost always come in small groups.  Then the albs will get curious or bored and make the same mistake.  I wish i could have taken a screen shot of this i wasnt thinking i was laughing to hard.  But there were close to 30 blodies lying around the area and not 1 was a hib.<br>
<br>
Please someone else try this in any BG and let me know how it worked out and if it was as fun for you too.  After a while the non-stealthers hear of this and start hanging out in the area and it become a slaughter fest.  Never had so much fun!!! <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unien.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Nien</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/11/02 10:07:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm22.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=183.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: inf spec vs. NS spec</span><hr size=1> I dunno if I've been lucky or not.  But I've had a pretty decent experience with my shade in the BG.<br>
